    <item>
      <title>Even More Wonderful Capsules</title>
      <author>LinlX</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/543330</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/543330#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">c1c33943de81d4aa1923b53d91c913914f6ee0af</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 02 Jan 2025 23:04:31 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66edb56d7b21a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66edb5759fbff.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66edb575d58f7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66edb575c764d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66edb575edfb6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66edb575e0778.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66edb576048d3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66ee5a52dfd65.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66ee5a52e81d6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66ee5a52ef281.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67771a9dc3516.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67771aa8f0f6a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Even More Wonderful Capsules (Major Update)&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Got rid of the "not enough space" error for large objects (except for the Rito Skyboat, since it is a static object, but it is easily extracted with an arrow). So now large objects can be extracted standing on the ground. Also, the model for the Large Sky Bonfire was improved and the Giant Plant capsule was added. Thanks to #1RijuFan, who made dynamic collisions for the Bargainer Statue, Horned Bargainer Statue, Giant Plant, they now have correct physics and the problem with the glue is gone.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div data-youtube-video=""&gt;&lt;iframe width="320" height="240" allowfullscreen="true" autoplay="false" disablekbcontrols="false" enableiframeapi="false" endtime="0" ivloadpolicy="0" loop="false" modestbranding="false" origin="" playlist="" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-gKOCR1IuMI" start="0"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is essentially an update of &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/497178"&gt;this previous capsule mod&lt;/a&gt;, but here a lot of work has been done to fix all the detected errors and several interesting capsules have been added such as &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/542819"&gt;Lord of the Mountain&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Mineru Construct&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Massive Cylindrical Gear&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Bargainer Statue&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Horned Bargainer Statue&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Golem Forge Shop&lt;/span&gt;, etc. And all objects are now dynamic, including Fires with Cooking Pots.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;stick&lt;/span&gt; some object to Beedle&lt;/span&gt;, it will also be possible to &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;move it&lt;/span&gt;. But be careful, if you then stick another object to it, the game will crash on the Switch console (not tested with emulators).&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66ee5a52ef281.jpg"&gt;&lt;br&gt;The main capsule shops can be purchased from the first &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/521692"&gt;Horned Statue&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Lookout Landing&lt;/span&gt;. Also in this mod, the inventory has been expanded by &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/506668"&gt;30 slots&lt;/a&gt; for all types of weapons and 120 slots for zonal devices.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Since the throw function with the "R" button is associated with a separate actor that is used only for throwing capsule actors and materials, for this reason, if you throw the &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/498516"&gt;Zonai Floating Platform&lt;/a&gt; from the quick menu, it is impossible to climb on it (when it was retrieved by throwing the "R" button). For most objects thrown with the R button, I added a catch function to return this capsule actor to the inventory. But the good thing is that I at least made this throw function work, unlike the old mod, I did not add throw and quick menu support for all capsules, but only for the most useful ones so as not to overload the quick menu.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1 class="SelectedElement"&gt;The mod is adapted only for the latest game update 1.2.1&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/even_more_wonderful_capsules-major_update.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/even_more_wonderful_capsules.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Gameplay</category>
      <category>Gameplay</category>
    </item>
