    <item>
      <title>Swap Sage Weapons</title>
      <author>#1RijuFan</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/563751</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/563751#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">8bf6264606a2931a1c6a1cc5d980555c9e8305e8</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Dec 2024 07:19:31 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb20eb81f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb20c2d1b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb20b5a17.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb20e8b89.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb20b47de.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb20b7ca1.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb20c9f5c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb209fb76.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6767bb2095386.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod allows you to give weapons to the sages during gameplay (except &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;Mineru, she can already wield fuses&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;br&gt;I wanted to do something for the winter season, so I created this mod. So... even though this mod is not winter themed...&amp;nbsp;Happy holidays!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For &lt;b&gt;Riju&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;Sidon&lt;/b&gt;, and &lt;b&gt;Yunobo&lt;/b&gt;, first make sure you are at a close distance, and then you can press ZL + X or B (the run button; depends on your run button setting) at the same time to give them your weapon, and subsequently take it back. Make sure to not hold ZL before pressing X, try to time the press so the buttons get pressed at the same time!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;For &lt;b&gt;Tulin&lt;/b&gt;, press ZL + X or B while in range with a bow equipped to give him your bow, and use the same button combo without a bow to give him a fuse for his arrows from your equipped weapon.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can give two weapons to Riju, so try different combinations out!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Also, the weapon data is stored at the end of the string array Pouch.KeyItem.Content.Name in the save data, so please don't worry about losing weapons due to saving/reloading.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There are two versions provided, the second of which is a version of the mod that restores the sages' original look, voice, physics, etc. Because the models and parameters have been changed to accomodate this mod's functionality, it will conflict with other Better Sages Mods currently available.&lt;br&gt;This mod also slightly modifies an assortment of weapons, but these changes are minimal and won't cause any notable breaking if overwritten by another mod or removed. Nevertheless, use TKMM to merge if you want to use a mod that edits the aforementioned file(s).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The mod should also work with modded weapons, though I have not explicitly tested this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Known issues:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;* Modifiers are erased and durability is restored when an item is transfered. I opted to "transfer" the weapon to the sages rather than having a drop/pickup system, which allows for more customizability, but prevents modifiers from being transferred for some reason.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* Sidon's animations don't work well with swords/greatswords, so they are attached on the end of a pole so I wouldn't have to completely re-animate Sidon. It is rigged unconventionally, so you may notice visual inconsistencies with some animations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* In addition, I wasn't able to get the fused weapon to show up in the right location on Sidon's back when you give him a sword or greatsword. There is a placeholder model shown instead.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* If you are in range of two sages at once, it will transfer to both in the same frame and potentially cause you to lose items. The interaction range is small for this very reason, but please be careful!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* In general, be wary of giving weapons to sages during the main story. There are rare cases where the game de-equips the sage and can cause a weapon to be lost permanently.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* If any sages have a weapon swapped when a boss is defeated as part of the main story, the boss explosion cutscene may infinite load (I experinced this with the Zora boss, but not Gerudo or Ganon; not sure about others). This can be fixed beforehand by desummoning sages with weapons, and for the sage of that dungeon, taking the weapon you gave them back.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* If Riju is sitting on her chair, she will delete any weapons you give her.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* For the sake of weapons looking nice when Riju sheaths them, I have changed some parameters for various weapons. This same parameter affects all NPCs, however, so it may be the case that sheath positions for other NPCs look odd (I have not seen this issue in-game yet.) If you would like to revert this change, remove the files starting with "Weapon_" from romfs/Pack/Actor (except for Weapon_Sword_152_Main and Weapon_Sword_152_Sub, those are Riju's weapons!)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* When you give Tulin an updated fuse for his arrow, he may need to shoot the arrow he already has prepared before the new fuse will take effect. (This is also why his first arrow is unfused when loading from a save.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Other mod trivia:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;* If you give away your master sword to a sage, the game will give you a new one when you save and reload.&lt;br&gt;* Sages can activate Zonai devices fused to their weapons without using Link's battery.&lt;br&gt;* Tulin has various quirks:&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;* If Tulin misses an arrow shot, there seems to be a chance the fused object he shoots will spawn. An unconventional way to duplicate items&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;* If Tulin has an AOE damage item for arrow fuses, such as a Ruby, the AOE damage will also hurt Link.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;* If Tulin gets hit during charging an arrow he drops the fuse, but this makes it invisible.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There are multiple RSTB provided in the System/Resource folder. If you are playing on console, be sure to delete the ones that don't match your version!&lt;br&gt;This mod was primarily tested on Console with v1.1.2. There may be crashes or issues with other configurations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/sageweaponswap.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/sageweaponswapreal.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Misc</category>
      <category>AI &amp; Events</category>
    </item>
