      <guid isPermaLink="false">0fe7b2f6389b48aa03c2f3bee2e63f1a8ad1a543</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 05 Dec 2024 18:02:03 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/674e1f28e50f2.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/674e1f50866af.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/674e1f50b7adb.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; New Discovery&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;I've been doing more research recently, and found that vanilla icons were generated with all bloom disabled (just like armor icons), and with color correction disabled. Additionally, I found that icons were generated at 576x576, then downscaled to 256x256. From this, I've found that the best ultracam resolution to use is 7680x4320, 4 times the vanilla resolution (1920x1080), since 576 is 4 times 144, the vanilla fuse icon size.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;Have you ever wanted to make accurate icons? Now you can! Head over to &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/tuts/18198"&gt;the tutorial&lt;/a&gt; to learn how to use this mod to make accurate icons for weapons, shields, and materials. Bows coming soon!</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/ultimate_icon_tool.7z" type="application/x-7z-compressed"/>
